gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Grizzlies 113, Bucks 110
gameRecap.excerpt: Memphis stuns Milwaukee, 113-110. For Memphis, GG Jackson (27 points, six 3PM-career high), Ziaire Williams (27 points-career high, four rebounds, four assists, four 3PM), and Vince Williams Jr. with his 3rd career double-double (18 points, 12 rebounds-career high, seven assists) combine for 72 to lead the way. Giannis Antetokounmpo led the way and recorded his 43rd double-double of the season with 35 points and 12 assists while Damian Lillard tallied 24 points, five rebounds, and seven assists for Milwaukee in the losing effort. Memphis wins and improves to 20-36 on the season, while Milwaukee moves to 35-21 with the loss.
